Galba became in this year proconsul of Africa and achieved consider- able success there.⁸ Claudius is stated to have anticipated and explained an eclipse falling on his birthday.⁴ Probably in this year took place the rebellion of Mithridates, king of Bosporus, who was defeated and driven from his kingdom in the following year by A. Didius Gallus, legatus of Moesia.⁸

M. Vinicius, the consul of the preceding year, was poisoned at the instigation of Messalina, who feared that he would take revenge upon her ior the murder of his wife Julia.⁸

Another conspiracy was formed in this year by Asinius Gallus, but proved to be insignificant, whence he escaped with the penalty of exile.⁹ Statilius Corvinus appears to have been joined with him, and the plot is said to have extended to the emperor's sreedmen and slaves.¹⁰
